# ModelBound skill authoring

When editing files in `skills/`, `.cursor/skills/`, `.agents/skills/`, or any `SKILL.md`:

1. **Preserve YAML frontmatter.** Never silently drop, rename, or blank the `name`, `description`, `version`, `model`, or `tags` keys.
2. **Token-conscious edits.** Prefer surgical edits over full rewrites. If a rewrite is necessary, propose running `/mb-optimize` afterward.
3. **Verify before commit.** After non-trivial edits, suggest `/mb-pipeline <skill>` so the user sees lint/trust/test/benchmark/optimize output before pushing.
4. **Never invent versions.** Use `/mb-versions <skill>` to look up real IDs before referencing them in commits or PRs.
5. **Restore is non-destructive.** Restoring an old version creates a new version on top of history; reassure the user nothing is lost.

When the user pastes a skill file into chat without a slug, ask whether they want a local diff (`/mb-optimize ./path`) or a cloud-tracked one (`/mb-optimize <slug>`).
